PN,31913
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1775830266
OL,3,CJames McAvoy 'wanted to make a popcorn
OL,4,Cmovie about people from council
OL,5,Cestates'
OL,7,FScottish McAvoy has something of a
OL,8,Fblended identity, with an American
OL,9,Fwife and two children raised in
OL,10,FEngland.
OL,12,FAhead of a summer which contains a
OL,13,Fmen's football World Cup, I want to
OL,14,Fknow which shirts are worn around the
OL,15,Fhouse and who he supports. James
OL,16,Flaughs before answering.
OL,18,F"Look, I would never wear an England
OL,19,Fshirt. I do support England, let it be
OL,20,Fknown."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31914
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1775830266
OL,3,CJames McAvoy 'wanted to make a popcorn
OL,4,Cmovie about people from council
OL,5,Cestates'
OL,7,F"My eldest is very much an England
OL,8,Ffan. I'm not one of those Scottish
OL,9,Fpeople who cheers against England.
OL,10,FI'll admit, I did that in my teens.
OL,11,FI'll cheer on England definitely, but
OL,12,Fthe only kit I'll ever wear is a
OL,13,FScotland kit."
OL,15,FCatch up on the latest entertainment
OL,16,Fnews with ITV's Unscripted podcast
OL,17,Fwith Nina Nannar
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/14
